<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-01T09:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-01T09:35:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20 Mission/7–144: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ford</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-01T18:00:00+03:25">July
                                        1, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received July 1—3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>472. Department’s 243, April 21. Although Legation has approached
                                Foreign Minister several times regarding renewal of agreement on
                                American Military Mission to Iranian <hi rend="italic">Gendarmerie</hi> no formal reply has been received. However,
                                Colonel Schwarzkopf today received letter from Minister of Interior
                                stating his desire that agreement be renewed for one additional
                                year. I shall continue to press Saed for formal statement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>